 144:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** /** @defgroup RCC_Exported_Functions_Group1 Initialization and de-initialization functions
 145:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *  @brief    Initialization and Configuration functions
 146:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *
 147:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** @verbatim
 148:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 149:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****            ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
 150:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 151:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
 152:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       This section provides functions allowing to configure the internal/external oscillators
 153:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (HSE, HSI, LSE, MSI, LSI, PLL, CSS and MCO) and the CPU and System buses clocks (SYSCLK, AHB1
 154:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****        AHB2, AHB3, AHB4, AHB5, APB1, APB2, APB4 and APB5).
 155:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 156:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] Internal/external clock and PLL configuration
 157:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) HSI (high-speed internal), 64 MHz factory-trimmed RC used directly or through
 158:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              the PLL as System clock source.
 159:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 160:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) MSI is a low-power RC oscillator which can be used directly as system clock, periphera
 161:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              clock, or PLL input.But even with frequency calibration, is less accurate than an
 162:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              external crystal oscillator or ceramic resonator.
 163:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 164:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) LSI (low-speed internal), 32 KHz low consumption RC used as IWDG and/or RTC
 165:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              clock source.
 166:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 167:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) HSE (high-speed external), 4 to 48 MHz crystal oscillator used directly or
 168:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              through the PLL as System clock source. Can be used also as RTC clock source.
 169:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 170:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) LSE (low-speed external), 32 KHz oscillator used as RTC clock source.
 171:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 172:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) PLL , The RCC features three independent PLLs (clocked by HSI , HSE or MSI),
 173:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              featuring three different output clocks and able  to work either in integer or Fractio
 174:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) A main PLL, PLL1, which is generally used to provide clocks to the CPU
 175:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****                 and to some peripherals via the ICx mux.
 176:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****            (++) Two dedicated PLLs, PLL2 and PLL3, which are used to generate the kernel clock for 
 177:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 178:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) HSE CSS (Clock security system), once enabled and if a HSE clock failure occurs
 179:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****             (HSE used directly or through PLL as System clock source), the System clock
 180:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              is automatically switched to HSI and an interrupt is generated if enabled.
 181:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The interrupt is linked to the Cortex-M NMI (Non-Maskable Interrupt)
 182:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              exception vector.
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccKuNIg1.s 			page 95


 183:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 184:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) LSE CSS (Clock security system), once enabled and if a LSE clock failure occurs
 185:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              the LSE is no more provided to RTC, it allows to wake-up from standby mode and protect
 186:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              backup registers and BKPSRAM via TAMP. The LSE CSS may be re-armed for further attempt
 187:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 188:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) MCO1 (micro controller clock output), used to output HSI, LSE, HSE, LSI, MSI, CPU (SYS
 189:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              or IC10 mux clock (through a configurable pre-scaler) on PA8 pin.
 190:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 191:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) MCO2 (micro controller clock output), used to output HSI, LSE, HSE, LSI, MSI, System B
 192:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              IC15 mux or IC20 mux clock (through a configurable pre-scaler) on PC9 pin.
 193:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 194:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] CPU, System bus, AHB and APB buses clocks configuration
 195:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          (#) Several clock sources can be used to drive independently the CPU (CPUCLK) and System b
 196:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              HSI, MSI, HSE or ICx mux.
 197:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              The AHB clock (HCLK) is derived from System core clock through configurable
 198:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              pre-scaler and used to clock the CPU, memory and peripherals mapped
 199:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              on AHB and APB bus through configurable pre-scalers
 200:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              and used to clock the peripherals mapped on these buses. You can use
 201:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****              "HAL_RCC_GetSysClockFreq()" function to retrieve system clock frequency.
 202:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 203:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c ****          -@- All the peripheral clocks are derived from the System bus clock (SYSCLK).
 204:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
